  "slug": "behind-whose-schedule-journal",
  "title": "Behind Whose Schedule?",
  "subtitle": "A journal prompt set for the always-catching-up feeling",
  "excerpt": "A journal prompt set for the woman who wakes up behind before the day has started. Asks whose schedule she is behind on, and whether that schedule was ever hers in the first place.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Written for homemade.education, drawing on time-poverty research and feminist writing on women's relationship with productivity and pace.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A journal prompt set for the behind-feeling that is already there before you have done anything wrong. The feeling that the day has started without you. These prompts ask who set the schedule you are failing to meet.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "New to journal prompts? Read ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "journal prompts as practice",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "/mindset/journal-prompts-as-practice"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " first.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The practice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Warm-up",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What does 'behind' feel like in your body when it arrives?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where do you notice it? What triggers it today?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When did the behind-feeling start for you? This morning, or earlier?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Trace it back to where it began. Is it today, or is it older than that?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Closer in",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behind whose schedule, exactly?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Name the specific schedule you are behind on. Your own? Someone else's? A version of yourself from five years ago? The person you thought you would be by now?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Did you ever agree to that schedule?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When was it set, and by whom? Was it chosen, or arrived at without choice?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What is one thing you could remove from today's schedule without real damage?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Not everything. One thing. Write it down and cross it off before you close the notebook.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this practice comes from",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Written for homemade.education. Draws on time-poverty research. The research shows that women carry more of the unpaid schedule than men. It also shows that women often measure themselves against a productivity ideal that was never set by or for them.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
